fix(deterrence): resolve asset URLs for cast, direct test path, real-motion pill

- MediaCaster.resolveAssetUrl() converts /assets/media/* to full
  http://<homey-ip>/app/<app-id>/asset/* URLs using homey.api.getLocalUrl(),
  so Chromecasts and other cast devices can actually fetch the bundled
  siren/dog-bark/blue-lights files.
- MediaCaster.startSiren() now prefers cast_url for audio on cast
  speakers (Google Home, Sonos via cast), falls back to speaker_playing.
- MediaCaster.startBlueLights() only routes to cast_url when the device
  truly has that capability, logs which device is targeted.
- DeterrenceEngine.runDirect(zoneId) is a test path that triggers media
  in the exact zone the user pressed, bypassing the reaction-zone matrix
  so Test avskrekking from a sensor-only zone no longer fires media
  in some other zone.
- app.testDeterrence() uses runDirect, keeps the 15s auto-stop.
- app.motionLastSeen + getRecentMotionZones() records real motion
  timestamps (before mode gating) and exposes zones with motion in
  the last 60 seconds.
- /status now returns recentMotionZones; dashboard pill logic uses it
  so BEVEGELSE only shows on actual sensor activity (not as a side
  effect of pressing the test button), and AVSKREKKING takes priority
  over motion on the same zone.
